   - The proof is by induction on the structure of `p`.
   - The case for `cons` (adding an edge to the front of the walk) requires considering whether the new vertex `v` was already in the support of the remaining walk `p₁`.

2. **Key Observations**:
   - The `supportSet` of `cons` is `insert v p₁.supportSet`.
   - The `edgeSet` of `cons` is `insert (s(v, p)) p₁.edgeSet`, where `(v, p)` is the new edge.
   - The induction hypothesis gives `p₁.supportSet.card ≤ p₁.edgeSet.card + 1`.
